Reasoning: 
- cs.CL (Computation and Language): The paper deals with natural language processing techniques such as word embedding and classification algorithms to identify concepts related to the restaurant domain. 
- cs.IR (Information Retrieval): The paper involves information extraction from unstructured text data related to the restaurant domain. 
- cs.LG (Machine Learning): The paper uses hierarchical clustering and classification algorithms to identify and classify domain-related words into concepts. 
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence): The paper involves the use of AI techniques such as word embedding and classification algorithms to automate the process of concept identification. 
- cs.DB (Databases): The paper mentions the creation of a semi-automatic ontology on the restaurant domain, which involves organizing and storing domain-related concepts in a structured manner.
